b'[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](av117.htm)  [Next](av119.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n## VI, 102. Charm to secure the love of a woman.\n\n1\\. As this draught animal, O ye Asvins, comes on, and proceeds, thus may thy\nsoul come on, and proceed to me!  \n2\\. I draw to myself thy mind, as the leading stallion the female side-horse.\nAs the stalk of grass torn by the wind, thus shall thy mind fasten itself upon\nme!  \n3\\. A coaxing mixture of salve, of sweet wood, of kushtha, and of spikenard,\ndo I deftly pick out with the hands of Bhaga (good fortune).\n\n\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: III, 25. Charm to arouse the passionate love of a woman](av119.htm)\n\n'